# CDK Core Packages — Rebuild Lambda Layer After Changes

Whenever you modify any file under `apps/cdk/src/core-packages/` (models, services, utilities, etc.) or any Lambda handler under `apps/cdk/src/lambda/`, you **must** rebuild the Lambda layer so the deployed Lambda picks up the changes.

## Required command

```bash
cd apps/cdk && yarn build:layer
```

Run this from the workspace root:

```bash
nx run cdk:build:layer
```

or directly:

```bash
cd apps/cdk && yarn build:layer
```

## When to run

- After editing any file in `apps/cdk/src/core-packages/rendasua_core_packages/` (models, hasura_client, utilities, etc.)
- After editing any Lambda handler in `apps/cdk/src/lambda/`
- Before deploying the CDK stack or pushing changes

## What it does

`build:layer` runs `src/lambda-layer/build-core-packages-layer.sh`, which packages `rendasua_core_packages` into a zip that AWS Lambda loads as a layer. Without rebuilding, Lambda will continue running stale code.
